{
  "id": "RHSA-2025:21232",
  "vendor": "Red Hat",
  "type": "Security Advisory (RHSA)",
  "title": "Red Hat Security Advisory: container-tools:rhel8 security update",
  "issuedDate": "2025-11-13T10:51:18+00:00",
  "updatedDate": "2025-11-13T10:51:18+00:00",
  "pubDate": "2025-11-13T10:51:18+00:00",
  "dateStr": "2025-11-13",
  "url": "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2025:21232",
  "severity": "Important",
  "overview": "An update for the container-tools:rhel8 module is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8.\n\nRed Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Important. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.",
  "description": "The container-tools module contains tools for working with containers, notably podman, buildah, skopeo, and runc.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* runc: container escape via 'masked path' abuse due to mount race conditions (CVE-2025-31133)\n\n* runc: container escape with malicious config due to /dev/console mount and related races (CVE-2025-52565)\n\n* runc: container escape and denial of service due to arbitrary write gadgets and procfs write redirects (CVE-2025-52881)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
  "affected_products": [
    "Red Hat Enterprise Linux",
    "Red Hat Enterprise Linux AppStream (v. 8)"
  ],
  "cves": [
    "CVE-2025-31133",
    "CVE-2025-52565",
    "CVE-2025-52881"
  ],
